# Instructions

1. Build the Dockerfile. Inside this directory run:

```
docker build -t ros2-jazzy-colcon .
```

2. Run the container while mounting the sdk-ros directory

```
docker run -it --name ros2_jazzy_dev --network host --rm \
  -v PATH_TO_SDK_ROS:/workspace/src \
  ros2-jazzy-colcon
```

3. Update apt and install dependencies

```
apt-get update
rosdep install --from-paths src --ignore-src -r -y
```

4. Build

```
colcon build
```

5. **[Recommended]** If you want to persist changes to avoid having to re-install and compile everything, commit the Docker container. From another terminal in the host machine run:

```
docker commit ros2_jazzy_dev ros2-jazzy-colcon:latest
```
